cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CR

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely sub-category as the paper deals with visual appearance-based person retrieval using computer vision techniques such as Mask R-CNN and DenseNet-169. 
2. cs.MM (Multimedia) is also likely as the paper deals with analyzing surveillance videos. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is likely as the paper proposes an algorithm for person retrieval using soft biometrics. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is likely as the paper uses fine-tuning of Mask R-CNN and DenseNet-169 for person detection and attribute classification respectively. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with surveillance and security-related applications.
